It is related that the late Lord Beauchamp used to say that he divided men into twoelasses, according as they believed, or did not believe, in the day of judge- ment. Certainly Bede would stand very high in the former class. The subject is ever in his thoughts, and he is continually urging his readers to bear it in their niinds⁷, and to prepare for the day of death, which will fix irrevocably their fate for weal or woe ⁸.
